 -2\frac{\partial^2 Y_0}{\partial x\,\partial\zeta}-\frac{\partial Y_0}{\partial x}-xY_0 
 Y_0=A_0 (x)+B_0 (x)e^{-\zeta} 
\displaystyle\frac{\partial Y_0}{\partial x} = A_0'(x)+B_0'(x)e^{-\zeta}
\displaystyle\frac{\partial^2 Y_0}{\partial x\partial\zeta} = \frac{\partial}{\partial\zeta}\frac{\partial Y_0}{\partial x} = -B_0'(x)e^{-\zeta}
